items.title: Rubio says the U.S. doesn’t need Venezuelan oil but seeks to deny adversaries control over it—and doesn’t rule out occupying the country
items.description: "What we're not going to allow is for the oil industry in Venezuela to be controlled by adversaries of the United States."

items.title: Rubio Stresses U.S. Plan to Coerce Venezuela Rather Than Govern It

items.title: The Venezuela I Know
items.description: Many are celebrating the ouster of a brutal dictator, but the Maduro regime may survive the loss of Maduro.

items.title: Venezuela’s capital Caracas is unusually quiet with stores and gas stations closed, a day after Maduro was deposed by U.S.
items.description: A day before, lines wound through stores and outside gas stations as uncertain Venezuelans stocked up on goods in case turmoil broke out.
